parameters.text:
=You extract a structured résumé from raw text. Output ONLY a JSON object matching this schema exactly:

{
  "contact": { "name": "", "title": "", "email": "", "phone": "", "location": "", "linkedin": "", "portfolio": "" },
  "summary_raw": "",
  "experience": [
    { "title": "", "company": "", "location": "", "start": "", "end": "", "current": false, "bullets": [""] }
  ],
  "education": [
    { "institution": "", "degree": "", "field": "", "location": "", "start": "", "end": "" }
  ],
  "skills": { "technical": [], "soft": [], "tools": [], "languages": [] },
  "certifications": [ { "name": "", "issuer": "", "year": "" } ]
}

Rules:
- Never invent facts. If a field isn't in the text, return an empty string or empty array.
- Dates as the candidate wrote them ("Jan 2022", "2020", etc.). Don't normalise.
- For each experience row, lift every bullet point as-is into "bullets".
- "current": true only if the text clearly says "Present", "Current", or no end date is given for the latest role.
- Output ONLY the JSON, no markdown fences, no commentary.

RÉSUMÉ TEXT:
{{ $json.resume_text }}

parameters.jsCode:
// Parse the LLM JSON output and merge in any user overrides (phone, linkedin, etc.)
let raw = $input.first().json.text || '';
raw = raw.trim();
if (raw.startsWith('```')) {
  raw = raw.replace(/^```(?:json)?\n?/, '').replace(/\n?```$/, '');
}
let parsed;
try {
  parsed = JSON.parse(raw);
} catch (e) {
  const match = raw.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
  if (!match) throw new Error('LLM did not return parseable JSON: ' + e.message);
  parsed = JSON.parse(match[0]);
}

const overrides = $('Webhook').first().json.body.user_overrides || {};
parsed.contact = parsed.contact || {};
for (const [k, v] of Object.entries(overrides)) {
  if (v && typeof v === 'string' && v.trim()) {
    parsed.contact[k] = v.trim();
  }
}

return [{ json: { resume_full_data: parsed } }];

// Fan out: one item per selected career, carrying the full resume + webhook body
const resume = $('Merge User Overrides').first().json.resume_full_data;
const body = $('Webhook').first().json.body;
const careers = body.selected_careers || [];
return careers.map((c) => ({
  json: {
    ...body,
    career: c,
    resume_full_data: resume,
  },
}));

// Build the must-include keyword list from enriched_jobs (capped at 25)
const enrichedItems = $('Fetch Enriched Jobs').all();
const enriched = enrichedItems.length > 0 ? enrichedItems[0].json : {};
const keywords = new Set();

(enriched.technical_skills || []).forEach(k => k && keywords.add(k));
(enriched.soft_skills || []).forEach(k => k && keywords.add(k));
(enriched.typical_tasks || []).forEach(k => k && keywords.add(k));
(enriched.certifications_requirements || '').split(/[,;\n]/).forEach(k => {
  const t = (k || '').trim();
  if (t) keywords.add(t);
});

// Fetch Personality Sections now returns ALL report_sections for the report
// (the n8n Supabase node doesn't support an "in" filter), so narrow to the
// four personality-relevant types here before stitching the LLM prompt block.
const PERSONALITY_TYPES = new Set(['approach', 'strengths', 'values', 'init_summary']);
const personality = $('Fetch Personality Sections').all()
  .filter(i => PERSONALITY_TYPES.has(i.json.section_type))
  .map(i => (i.json.content || '').trim())
  .filter(Boolean)
  .join('\n\n---\n\n');

const narrativeItems = $('Fetch Career Narrative').all();
const narrative = narrativeItems.length > 0 ? (narrativeItems[0].json.content || '') : '';

const current = $('Split In Batches').item.json;

return [{
  json: {
    ...current,
    keywords: Array.from(keywords).slice(0, 25),
    personality_voice: personality,
    career_narrative: narrative,
  },
}];

parameters.text:
=You re-frame a candidate's existing résumé toward a specific target career.

NEVER invent facts. NEVER add experience the candidate doesn't have. Your job is to choose which existing bullets to lift, re-order them, and rewrite the summary so the résumé tells the strongest possible story for THIS target.

Output ONLY a JSON object matching this schema (no markdown, no commentary):

{
  "contact": {},
  "summary": "",
  "experience": [
    { "title": "", "company": "", "location": "", "start": "", "end": "", "current": false, "bullets": [""] }
  ],
  "skills_grouped": {
    "technical": [], "tools": [], "soft": [], "languages": []
  },
  "education": [],
  "certifications": [],
  "highlights": [""]
}

Rules:
- contact: copy from input unchanged.
- summary: 3-4 sentences, written in the voice cues provided. Lead with the strongest claim to the target role. Avoid clichés ("results-driven", "passionate").
- experience: keep every role the candidate held. Within each role, re-order bullets to lead with what matters for the target. You can rewrite phrasing (active voice, quantify if the number is already in the source) but never fabricate metrics.
- skills_grouped: distribute into technical / tools / soft / languages buckets, prioritising overlap with the keyword list.
- education: copy unchanged. If the input has no education, omit the education key entirely (do not emit an empty array or stub entries).
- certifications: copy unchanged. If the candidate has no real certifications in the input résumé and none surfaced from the assessment, OMIT the certifications key entirely. Do NOT invent a stub like {name: "AI for Business", issuer: "", year: ""} — leaving it out is better than rendering an empty section.
- highlights: 2-3 standout one-liners pulled from experience.

LANGUAGE: Write the entire résumé (all section content and headings) in the user's preferred language.
preferred_language = {{ $('Webhook').first().json.body.preferred_language }}
If preferred_language is 'nl', write in Dutch (informal je-form, Dutch number/date formatting: €1.500, dd-mm-jjjj); for any other value, write in English. Keep proper nouns, company names, and widely-English job titles as-is. No em-dashes; use commas, colons, parentheses, or sentence breaks.

TARGET CAREER: {{ $json.career.career_title }}

WHY-SUITED NARRATIVE (from their assessment, optional):
{{ $json.career_narrative || 'Not available.' }}

PERSONALITY VOICE CUES:
{{ $json.personality_voice || '' }}

MUST-INCLUDE KEYWORDS (try to land these):
{{ JSON.stringify($json.keywords) }}

CANDIDATE'S CURRENT RÉSUMÉ (JSON):
{{ JSON.stringify($json.resume_full_data) }}

parameters.jsCode:
// Assemble the final payload for the custom_resumes row update.
// Resume-only flow: cover letters now live in the dedicated WF_cover_letter
// workflow, so this no longer reads or generates a cover letter.

function safeParseJson(raw) {
  if (raw == null) return null;
  if (typeof raw === 'object') return raw;
  let s = String(raw).trim();
  if (s.startsWith('```')) {
    s = s.replace(/^```(?:json)?\n?/, '').replace(/\n?```$/, '');
  }
  try { return JSON.parse(s); }
  catch (e) {
    const m = s.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
    return m ? JSON.parse(m[0]) : null;
  }
}

const atsRaw = $('ATS Optimisation Pass').item.json.text;
const ats = safeParseJson(atsRaw);
if (!ats) throw new Error('Could not parse ATS pass output');

// LLM sometimes nests resume as a stringified {resume_json: "..."}, sometimes as
// an object. Force it to an object so the frontend can read .contact / .experience.
const resumeJsonObj = (ats.resume_json && typeof ats.resume_json === 'object')
  ? ats.resume_json
  : safeParseJson(ats.resume_json);

// Legacy prompts wrote the resume at the top level (no nested resume_json).
const finalResumeJson = resumeJsonObj || (ats.contact ? ats : null);
if (!finalResumeJson) throw new Error('ATS pass output had no resume_json');

const career = $('Build Keyword List').item.json.career;

return [{
  json: {
    custom_resume_id: career.custom_resume_id,
    resume_json: finalResumeJson,
    cover_letter_json: null,
    ats_score: ats.ats_score,
    keyword_coverage: ats.keyword_coverage,
  },
}];

// Preserve original webhook payload alongside extracted résumé text
return [{
  json: {
    ...$('Webhook').first().json.body,
    resume_text: $input.first().json.text || '',
  },
}];

